# Backend General Conventions

- Python 3.12, use modern syntax (`X | None` instead of `Optional[X]`, `list[str]` instead of `List[str]`)
- Everything must be async — database operations, file I/O, endpoints
- Use ruff for linting/formatting (line-length 120)
- All backend code lives under `backend/` with application code in `backend/app/`
- Use custom exceptions from `app.core.exceptions` — never raise raw `HTTPException` in business logic
- Use `uuid.UUID` for all entity IDs
- Imports should use absolute paths from `app` (e.g. `from app.models.user import User`)
